2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses deep learning techniques for predicting the local parameters of cost volume aggregation process. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper uses deep learning techniques for solving a computer vision problem, which falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence. 
4. cs.RO (Robotics) - Dense stereo matching is an important problem in robotics, as it is used for tasks such as obstacle avoidance and navigation. 
5. cs.CVPR (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper presents a new approach for dense stereo matching, which is a topic of interest in the CVPR community.
